3. Install
----------

Do this:

    $ cd removable-media-utilities-1.0a0
    $ mkdir "=build"
    $ cd "=build"

to inspect the available configuration options:

    $ ../configure --help

then do it:

    $ ../configure [options]
    $ make
    $ make tests
    $ make install

  The  Makefile supports  the  DESTDIR environment  variable to  install
files in a temporary location, example: to see what will happen:

    $ make -n install DESTDIR=/tmp/marco/removable-media-utilities

to really do it:

    $ make install DESTDIR=/tmp/marco/removable-media-utilities


